Philippines Stocks: Atlas Mining, Metropolitan Bank, Vista Land

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-08-12T04:28:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/philippines-stocks-atlas-mining-metropolitan-bank-vista-land.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index gained 0.3 percent to
4,321.73, trimming this week’s decline to 2.6 percent. The
measure rounded its sharpest weekly loss since Feb. 25.  Miners:  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp climbed 4.7 percent to 20.85 pesos, the sharpest gain since
July 7 and pacing gains among the nation’s metals producers, as
copper rallied for a second day.  Manila Mining Corp. (MA)  Class A
shares (MA PM), which are reserved for Filipinos, increased 2.9
percent to 7 centavos.  Copper for delivery in three months rose as much as 1.2
percent in  London  to $8,990 and last traded at $8,918.75 a ton.
The metal jumped 3.3 percent yesterday.  Metropolitan Bank & Trust (MBT)  Co, the nation’s
second-largest bank by assets, increased 1.8 percent to 75.70
pesos, the highest close since Aug. 5. The bank posted an 83
percent increase in second-quarter net income to 3 billion pesos
($70 million), a stock-exchange filing today showed.  Vista Land & Lifescapes Inc. (VLL)   rose 1.2 percent to
3.29 pesos. The shares have rallied 7.2 percent since Aug. 10,
the biggest three-day gain since May 18. The homebuilder said it
bought back 865,000 shares in the open market at 3.15 pesos
each.  To contact the reporter on this story:
